ProMED-mail
promed@promedmail.org
[Quarantines are nasty problems to sort out. Considering recent instances
(plum pox potyvirus [PPVin North America, the interception of PPV-infected
plant tissues at the Sydney Airport), it is reasonable to err on the side of
caution. I am surprised that Australia has remained free of the pathogen
(_Erwinia amylovora_). Do any of our Australian subscribers know whether
the pathogen has ever been detected in Australia? Have any plants ever been
identified as infected with the pathogen in the natural state? What is the
history of quarantine against importing apples into Australia? - Mod.DH
